DataElement.preferredName: Person Reproductive History Assessment Description Text
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Person; a human being._An account of all reproductive events and problems a person has experienced. An important aggregate factor in epidemiological studies of women's health.  The concept usually includes the number and timing of pregnancies and their outcomes, the incidence of breast feeding, and may include age of menarche and menopause, regularity of menstruation, fertility, gynecological or obstetric problems, or contraceptive usage. (from On-line Medical Dictionary)_The final result of a determination of the value, significance, or extent of._A written or verbal account, representation, statement, or explanation of something._The words of something written.
